# Workflow design system guardrails

Apply these standards for any UI change in this repository:

- For primary actions (`Create`, `Save`, `Run`, `Approve`, `Convert`, `Send`), use the CI color token (`var(--arscmp-primary)`) via shared button styles/components. Avoid ad-hoc brand hex values in page-level classes.
- New workflow pages (especially create/detail/action pages) should include a step-guided header (`Step 1/2/3`) and a clear action area.
- Prefer reusable primitives and existing shells before new one-off markup:
  - shared page shell/panel patterns
  - shared button variants for primary/secondary/tertiary actions
  - shared step header blocks
- Keep visual language consistent:
  - rounded panel containers, soft border/shadow
  - strong primary CTA, quieter secondary actions
  - concise instructional copy above complex forms
- If touching an older page, move it toward this design language in-place without changing business logic.

## Quick examples

```tsx
// Preferred primary action
<button className="rounded-xl bg-[var(--arscmp-primary)] px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-semibold text-white">
  Save draft
</button>
```

```tsx
// Preferred workflow intro pattern
<section className="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
  <p className="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-zinc-500">Workflow</p>
  <div className="mt-4 grid gap-2 sm:grid-cols-3">{/* Step 1/2/3 cards */}</div>
</section>
```
